<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1821" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1821">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 871.001F37/3</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Vopicka</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 143.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith a
                            letter sent to the President of the United States by King Ferdinand of
                            Roumania.</p>
                        <p>I also enclose an office copy of said letter together with English
                            translation of same.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles J. Vopicka</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Translation.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">King <persName type="from">Ferdinand</persName> to
                                    President <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Very Dear and Great Friend</hi>: I fulfill a
                                very painful duty in announcing to you the cruel loss which Roumania
                                has just experienced in the person of its venerated Sovereign, His
                                Majesty King Carol I, my beloved Uncle, who expired at Pelesh Castle
                                on Saturday October 10th last. The good relations which have always
                                existed between our two countries gives me the assurance that you
                                will share the profound sorrow into which this sad event plunges me
                                and the whole of the Roumanian people.</p>
                            <p>Called by the order of succession to the throne of Roumania, I inform
                                you that I have taken the constitutional oath and ask you to be
                                assured that all my efforts will tend to the cultivation of the good
                                relations that exist between the United States of America and
                                Roumania. I seize with eagerness this circumstance to offer to you,
                                Mr. President, the expression of the sentiments of sincere esteem
                                and of high consideration with which I am,</p>
                            <p>Very dear and great friend,</p>
                            <p>Your Good Friend,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ferdinand</hi></signed>. <lb/>
                                <dateline rendition="#left">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName type="city">Bucharest</placeName>
                                            <placeName type="venue">Palace</placeName></hi></placeName>, <lb/>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-17"><hi rend="italic">This 17 October, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Porumbaro</hi></signed>. </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>